news.title: UK's Vistry to buy back shares worth $171 million
news.para: The UK rate cut in August - the first by the Bank of England in more than four years - potentially signals relief for struggling builders and homebuyers, after the new Labour government's push for aggressive planning reforms had boosted sentiment in the sector.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto rise 0.6% in August 2024
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales increased 0.6% in August following a drop of 0.8% in July, according to Toronto Regional Real Estate Board (TRREB) data.

news.title: Britain: Barratt's pre-tax profit dips by over 56% to $504.7 million in June 2024
news.para: The UK housing market outlook has turned more optimistic than it was three or six months ago, but demand continues to be sensitive to mortgage affordability, CEO David Thomas told Reuters.

news.title: PMRDA to cancel water affidavit mandate for new housing projects in Pune
news.para: Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) commissioner Yogesh Mhase, in a new circular issued on Tuesday, cancelled the authority’s previous order mandating affidavits from developers to ensure water supply to the residents in new housing projects.

news.title: CREDAI Bengaluru urges government to implement reforms in real estate development
news.para: The key areas of focus include providing clarity on the transferable development rights (TDR) issue that has been long pending and simplifying the regulations. The CREDAI Bengaluru opines that it

news.title: Delhi HC takes suo motu action on property mutation issues in urbanised villages
news.para: For years, these residents have faced regular harassment while repairing or renovating their old homes or arranging funds by keeping these properties mortgaged.

news.title: Interarch Building Products to invest Rs 95 crore to set up plant in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: In a statement on Wednesday, the company said it has inaugurated the first phase of this plant at district Nellore in Andhra Pradesh.

news.title: China plans to cut mortgage rates to shield banks
news.para: Financial regulators have proposed reducing rates on outstanding mortgages by a total of about 80 basis points (bps), part of a package that includes an accelerated timeline for when mortgages become eligible for refinancing, according to people familiar with the matter.

news.title: Suzlon Energy sells its headquarters in Pune for Rs 440 crore
news.para: Suzlon Energy has sold its Pune headquarters, One Earth, for Rs 440 crore to OE Business Park Pvt Ltd and leased it back for up to five years. This move is part of Suzlon's strategy to monetize non-core assets and reinvest in its core business, supporting its growth and expanding orderbook.

news.title: SC grants interim protection from arrest to Mumbai-based builder in cheating case
news.para: The order was passed on Rajesh Jain's appeal against Bombay high court's Aug 26 order that rejected his pre-arrest bail plea. Justices Sudhanshu Dhulia and Ahsanuddin Amanullah issued notice to complainant Dr Bharati Patil and posted the hearing on Oct 25.

news.title: Centre approves eight lakh PMAY houses in Chhattisgarh
news.para: ​The CM also informed that his government, which assumed office nine months ago, has requested the Centre to approve houses under PMAY separately for surrendered Naxalites and people affected by Maoist violence in the state.

news.title: CapitaLand Investment aims to double fund under management by 2028
news.para: ​In a statement, the company said it is targeting to more than double its FUM in its core market India by 2028, up from 7.4 billion Singapore dollars (Rs 458.8 billion) as on June 30, 2024.

news.title: SC asks Sahara Group to furnish list of top officials, properties for sale
news.para: A bench of Justices Sanjiv Khanna, M M Sundresh and Bela M Trivedi said the court has to find some practical solution for refunding the investors' money as the issue is pending for over a decade.

news.title: Max Estates raises Rs 800 crore through QIP for growth capital
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Tuesday, Max Estates informed that it has allotted nearly 1.34 crore shares to investors at a price of Rs 597.50 a piece.

news.title: Belagavi civic body's resolution to pay compensation comes under scrutiny
news.para: BCC passed a unanimous resolution to pay Rs 20 crore compensation to the land losers for the 80ft width road in the Shahapur area, which had been made without following the land acquisition procedures.

news.title: Raipur smart city chief expresses dissatisfaction over slow progress of STP projects
news.para: Commissioner Abinash Mishra of Raipur Municipal Corporation has criticized the slow construction of three Sewage Treatment Plants under Raipur Smart City Limited. These plants are essential for improving pond hygiene, which many residents rely on daily.

news.title: SCDRC quashes Ludhina development body's non-construction charge on plot
news.para: The commission, while quashing the demand of Rs 26.5 lakh as non-construction charges raised by GLADA, directed the authority to approve the building plan applied by complainant Avtar Kaur, 75, within 30 days from the date of receipt of copy of the order without any demand for non-construction charges.

news.title: Maharashtra CM kicks off Ramabai slum redevelopment project
news.para: The colony, spanning 33.15 hectares and housing around 17,000 tenements, is slated for redevelopment under the Slum Rehabilitation Authority, with MMRDA executing the project.
